<topic xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0">
    <title>inherit-environment()</title>
    <informaltable frame="topbot" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
        <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec colnum="1" colwidth="40pt"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry>Type:</entry>
                    <entry>yes|no</entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>Default:</entry>
                    <entry>yes</entry>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
    <para><emphasis role="bold">Description:</emphasis> By default, when <parameter>program()</parameter> starts an external application or script, it inherits the entire environment of the parent process (that is, &abbrev;). Use <userinput>inherit-environment(no)</userinput> to prevent this.</para>
</topic>
